<p>is a Research Assistant Professor at the Virginia Modelling, Analysis, and Simulation Center at Old Dominion University. He received his PhD in Modeling and Simulation at ODU in 2012. With a background in modeling and simulation, and applications of virtual and extended reality, he focuses on providing solutions and tools that address the paradigm shift in how we live, work, learn, and interact with one another as well as with autonomous and digital platforms. He works with the Commonwealth Center for Advanced Manufacturing on providing inclusive and accessible interfaces for people with special needs. He also collaborates with local artists on initiatives at the intersection of art, engineering, and science to enhance accessibility and inclusions by going beyond visualizations to achieve multi-sensory experiences.</p>
